localizations.en.title: Potty Training Song | CoComelon Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
localizations.en.description:
J.J. is ready to use the potty!  Sing along as his family helps him learn how!
Subscribe for new videos every week: https://www.youtube.com/c/cocomelon?sub_confirmation=1

Lyrics:

When you get that funny feeling
Way down low
Just stop what you’re doing
And go go go!

What are you doing?  Where did you go?
What are you doing?  I want to know!
I went to the potty, and washed my hands too
I went to the potty like the big kids do!

How do I do that?  How do I go? 
How do I do that?  I want to know!
Just sit on the potty, sit and wait
Sit on the potty and it will be great!

I’m sitting on the potty, ready to go
But nothing is happening, and why, I don’t know
Try again later, it’s okay,
Try again later, later today

I’ve got the funny feeling, way down low
I’ve got the funny feeling, I think I have to go!
Just sit on the potty, sit and wait
Sit on the potty and it will be great!

I went to the potty!  Look and see!
I went to the potty, hooray for me!
Great job, J.J., now wash your hands!
Great job, J.J., now do the potty dance!

Great job, J.J., do the potty dance
I/we got you some big boy underpants
When you get that funny feeling way down low, 
Stop what you’re doing and go, go, go!

title: The Ant and the Grasshopper | CoComelon Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
description: The Ant and the Grasshopper teach us an important lesson about hard work! Let's sing along to this classic tale! Subscribe for new ...
localizations.en.title: The Ant and the Grasshopper | CoComelon Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
localizations.en.description:
The Ant and the Grasshopper teach us an important lesson about hard work! Let’s sing along to this classic tale!
Subscribe for new videos every week: https://www.youtube.com/c/cocomelon?sub_confirmation=1

Lyrics:

In the summer the ants were a-working
Bringing food to their hill every day
While the grasshopper sang in the sunshine
On his fiddle, his song he did play.

“Fi-de-di, de-dah-doo, dah-de da-do
Fi-de-do, de-da-dee, de-da-day
I will sing all the while ‘neath the sunshine!
‘Neath the moon, I will dance, I will play!”

In the autumn the ants were still working
But the grasshopper still did not care
The ants asked “Why don’t you store food for winter?”
“When it’s cold, you’ll have no food to spare.”

“Fi-de-di, de-dah-doo, dah-de da-do
Fi-de-do, de-da-dee, de-da-day
‘Bove us all, there will always be sunshine
And there always will be time to play!”

Time went by, and along came the winter
And the wind gave a cold icy chill
Snow fell down, and there was no more sunshine
So the grasshopper went up the hill.

“Fi-de-di, de-dah-doo, dah-de da-do
Fi-de-do, de-da-dee, de-da-day
I am cold, I am wet, I am hungry
And I’m sorry I played the days away.”

In the valley he went to the anthill
He was cold, and embarrassed, and sad
But the ants told him that he was welcome
Then he thanked them and felt really glad!

“Fi-de-di, de-dah-doo, dah-de da-do
Fi-de-do, de-da-dee, de-da-day!”
And the grasshopper said in future seasons
Work comes first, then he’ll have time to play!

localizations.en.title: Doctor Checkup Song (School Version) | CoComelon Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
localizations.en.description:
Cody’s mom is a doctor! And she’s visiting Melon Patch Academy to show the class what she does so kids can be healthy today and tomorrow!
Subscribe for new videos every week: https://www.youtube.com/c/cocomelon?sub_confirmation=1

Lyrics:

When you go see the doctor
For your checkup today
She’ll make sure you’re healthy
In every way

She’ll check your weight, she’ll check your height
She’ll check to see that you’re growing right

When you go see the doctor
For your checkup today
She’ll make sure you’re healthy
In every way

She’ll check your lungs, she’ll check your heart
She’ll make sure they’re working, every part

When you go see the doctor
For your checkup today
She’ll make sure you’re healthy
In every way

She’ll check your eyes, she’ll check your ears
She’ll check how well you see and hear

When you go see the doctor
For your checkup today
She’ll make sure you’re healthy
In every way

She’ll check your mouth, she’ll check your throat
She’ll look at her checklist and make some notes

When you go see the doctor
For your checkup today
She’ll make sure you’re healthy
In every way

She’ll check your reflex, she’ll check your bones
To see that they’re healthy, and how much you’ve grown

When you go see the doctor
For your checkup today
She’ll make sure you’re healthy
In every way

Now she might say that you need a shot
But don’t be scared, it won’t hurt a lot

When you go see the doctor
For your checkup today
She’ll make sure you’re healthy
In every way

localizations.en.description:
Going on a doggy hunt! Its Bingo's Birthday but where has he gone? Can you help JJ find Bingo the dog? Sing along with the CoComelon family to popular nursery rhymes for kids!

Lyrics:
Going on a doggy hunt.
Going to catch my best friend.
He’s gonna love it.
Look, what’s up ahead?

Mud!

Can’t go over it
Can’t go under it
Can’t go through it
I gotta go around it!
Sloshy slosh, sloshy slosh.

Going on a doggy hunt.
Going to catch my best friend.
He’s gonna love it.
Look, what’s up ahead?

Party Goodies!

Can’t go over it
Can’t go through it
Can’t go around it
I gotta go under it!
Swish swash, swish swash

Going on a doggy hunt.
Going to catch my best friend.
He’s gonna love it.
Look, what’s up ahead?

Wind!

Can’t go over it
Can’t go under it
Can’t go around it
I gotta go through it!
Whoosh woo whoosh woo!

Going on a doggy hunt.
Going to catch my best friend.
He’s gonna love it.
Look, what’s up ahead?


Oh look! On the couch! 
What’s this?

Something funny.
With a long soft thing on its end
With two big ears
And a cold wet nose

Slightly longer interlude
It’s Bingo!.

Slurpy slurp, slurpy slurp.

C’mon Bingo! I have a surprise for you!

Run through the wind! 
Go under Dad! 
Slosh around the mud! 
And give your best dog a… a... 

Huh?...

Happy Birthday
Happy Birthday
Happy Birthday
To our good dog!
*bark bark*

description: Look out! Here comes the Big Bad Wolf! The three little pigs each hide in their houses made of hay, sticks, and brick, but will they ...
localizations.en.title: Three Little Pigs | CoComelon Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
localizations.en.description:
Look out!  Here comes the Big Bad Wolf!  The three little pigs each hide in their houses made of hay, sticks, and brick, but will they be strong enough to stand up to the wolf’s huffing and puffing?  
Subscribe for new videos every week: https://www.youtube.com/c/cocomelon?sub_confirmation=1

Lyrics:
 
Three little pigs went out one day
One built a house made out of hay
The other pigs thought it would fall, fall, fall
But the first didn’t care at all.
 
Three little pigs went out one day
The second used sticks to build away
The third pig thought it would fall, fall, fall
But the second didn’t care at all.
 
Three little pigs went out one day
For the third pig, bricks were the way
He knew the house wouldn’t fall, fall, fall
So the work didn’t bother him at all.
 
Then came a wolf who was big and bad
He was incredibly hungry and mad
The three little pigs saw the wolf that day
They slammed their doors and hid away
 
“Little pig, little pig, let me in!”
“Not by the hair on my chinny-chin chin!”
“Then I’ll huff and I’ll puff, and I’ll blow, blow, blow!”
And boy, did the hay house go!
 
“Little pigs, little pigs, let me in!”
“Not by the hair on our chinny-chin chins!”
“Then I’ll huff and I’ll puff, and I’ll blow, blow, blow!”
And boy, did the stick house go!
 
“Little pigs, little pigs, let me in!”
“Not by the hair on our chinny-chin chins !”
“Then I’ll huff and I’ll puff, and I’ll blow, blow, blow!”
But the bricks surely did not go!
 
The wolf was at his wit’s end, you see
He climbed on the roof, down the brick chimney!
He came with his teeth all bared, bared, bared
So the three little pigs got scared!
 
The third little pig lit a log on fire
The smoke started rising, higher and higher
The wolf burned his hairy tail, OW! OW! OW!
And the wolf ran out of town!
 
The two little piggies of hay and sticks
Learned a lesson all about work and bricks
A hard-worked job won’t fall fall fall
To a huff, or a puff, at all!
 
The three little pigs went out that day
Now they were free to laugh and play
The Big Bad Wolf was gone gone gone
And the little pigs danced ‘til dawn!

We also make life easier for parents who want to keep their kids happily entertained, giving you the peace of mind that your children are receiving quality educational content.  Our videos also give you an opportunity to teach and play with your children as you both watch!

localizations.en.description:
Oh no!  One of the dinosaur eggs rolled away and got stuck in a tree!  Now all the little dinos will have to work together as a team to get it down safely.

Subscribe for new videos every week: https://www.youtube.com/c/Cocomelon?sub_confirmation=1

Lyrics:
Dinos as lively as they can be
But one egg’s stuck in a tree
Get it down
Dinos as lively as they can be
They have ideas, you see
Dinos, they work as a dino team
But they have trouble it seems
Getting eggy out from the tree
Dinos, why don’t you see
If there’s another idea.

Dinos they jump all at once to see
If a quake will shake the tree
Boom! Boom! Boom!
Oopsie! The fruits fell right out the tree
Sticky as fruits can be!
Dinos, they work as a dino team
But they have trouble it seems
Getting eggy out from the tree
Dinos, why don’t you see
If there’s another idea.

Dinos they swing like in a trapeze
They think that this is a breeze!
Whoa! Whoa! WHOA!
Hey now! Don’t let go so quick-a-ly!
Look, now! You just missed the tree!
Dinos, they work as a dino team
But they have trouble it seems
Getting eggy out from the tree
Dinos, why don’t you see
If there’s another idea.

Dinos, they stack one on top of each
Stretching, just so they can reach
Poor Eggy!
Whoa there! You think you can reach the top?
Yippee! Be careful, don’t drop!
Dinos, they finally did succeed
Working as a dino team!
They got Eggy out from the tree
Dinos why don’t you see
What is inside the last egg!

localizations.en.title: "No No" Bedtime Song | CoComelon Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
localizations.en.description:
Oh no! The baby doesn’t want to get ready for bed!  His big sister will have to try to convince him with the help of their stuffed animal friends!  Enjoy this original tune, the sequel to the Yum Yum Vegetables Song!
Subscribe for new videos every week: https://www.youtube.com/c/cocomelon?sub_confirmation=1

Lyrics: 

Brush, brush, it’s time to brush your teeth!
No, no, no, I don’t want to brush my teeth!
Please, please!  Brushing is good for you!
No, no, no, I don’t like it, ew!
See, see, Teddy likes to brush!
One, two, three!  Almost clean, you see!
No, no, no, that’s mine!  I’ll brush them now!
Brush, brush, brush, they’re all clean, wow!

Bath, bath, it’s time to take a bath!
No, no, no, I don’t want to take a bath!
Please, please!  The bath is good for you!
No, no, no, I don’t like it, ew!
See, see, Elephant likes the bath!
One, two, three!  Almost clean, you see!
No, no, no, it’s mine!  I’ll take it now!
Splash, splash, splash, I like it, wow!

Pajamas, pajamas, it’s time to wear pajamas!
No, no, no, I don’t want to wear pajamas!
Please, please!  The pajamas are good for you!
No, no, no, I don’t like them, ew!
See, see, Monkey likes pajamas!
One, two, three!  Almost on, you see!
No, no, no, they’re mine!  I’ll wear them now!
Soft, soft, soft, I like them, wow!

Bed, bed, it’s time to get in bed!
No, no, no, I don’t want to get in bed!
Please, please!  Sleep is good for you!
No, no, no, I don’t like it, ew!
See, see, Mousy likes the bed!
One, two, three!  Cozy warm, you see!
No, no, no, it’s mine!  I’ll get in now!
Cozy, cozy, cozy, I like it, wow!

Story, story, it’s time to read a story!
No, no, no, I don’t want to read the story!
Please, please!  The story’s fun for you!
No, no, no, I don’t want to, ew!
See, see, Teddy reads the story!
One, two, three!  Almost done, you see!
No, no, no, it’s mine!  I’ll read it now!
Fun, fun, fun, I like it, wow!

At Cocomelon, our goal is to help make learning a fun and enjoyable experience for kids by creating beautiful 3D animation, educational lyrics, and toe-tapping music. 

Kids will laugh, dance, sing, and play along with our videos, learning letters, numbers, animal sounds, colors, and much, much more while simply enjoying our friendly characters and fun stories.

We also make life easier for parents who want to keep their kids happily entertained, giving you the peace of mind that your children are receiving quality educational content.  Our videos also give you an opportunity to teach and play with your children as you both watch!

Where kids can be happy and smart!

About Cocomelon:

Where kids can be happy and smart!

At Cocomelon, our goal is to help make learning a fun and enjoyable experience for kids by creating beautiful 3D animation, educational lyrics, and toe-tapping music. 

Kids will laugh, dance, sing, and play along with our videos, learning letters, numbers, animal sounds, colors, and much, much more while simply enjoying our friendly characters and fun stories.

We also make life easier for parents who want to keep their kids happily entertained, giving you the peace of mind that your children are receiving quality educational content.  Our videos also give you an opportunity to teach and play with your children as you both watch!

About Cocomelon:

Where kids can be happy and smart!

At Cocomelon, our goal is to help make learning a fun and enjoyable experience for kids by creating beautiful 3D animation, educational lyrics, and toe-tapping music. 

Kids will laugh, dance, sing, and play along with our videos, learning letters, numbers, animal sounds, colors, and much, much more while simply enjoying our friendly characters and fun stories.

We also make life easier for parents who want to keep their kids happily entertained, giving you the peace of mind that your children are receiving quality educational content.  Our videos also give you an opportunity to teach and play with your children as you both watch!

title: Santa JJ Song | CoComelon Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
description: HO HO HO Santa JJ is here! What do you want in your sock for Christmas! Sing along to your favorite Holiday Songs for kids!
localizations.en.title: Santa JJ Song | CoComelon Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs
localizations.en.description:
HO HO HO Santa JJ is here! What do you want in your sock for Christmas! Sing along to your favorite Holiday Songs for kids!
Subscribe for new videos every week!
https://www.youtube.com/c/CoComelon?sub_confirmation=1

Lyrics:
Jolly old Saint Nicholas
Lean your ear this way;
Don't you tell a single soul
What I'm going to say,
Christmas Eve is coming soon;
Now you dear old man,
Whisper what you'll bring to me;
Tell me if you can.

Ho Ho Ho!

When the clock is striking twelve,
When I'm fast asleep,
Down the chimney broad and black
With your pack you'll creep;
All the stockings you will find
Hanging in a row;
Mine will be the shortest one;
You'll be sure to know.

Ho Ho Ho!

Mom and dad want grown up things
YoYo wants a dolly
TomTom wants a story book,
Christmas sure is jolly
As for me, it’s getting late
This ole Christmas night
Choose for me, dear Santa Claus,
What you think is right.

Jolly old Saint Nicholas
Lean your ear this way;
Don't you tell a single soul
What I'm going to say,
Christmas Day is here at last
And it’s time to see
What you brought to me last night
Underneath our tree

Ho Ho Ho!
